The paper discusses the intersection of Natural Language Processing (NLP), cognitive science, and physics, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The workshop also explores theoretically motivated approaches to understanding word meanings and their interactions, which could fall under the sub-categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
